{     Summary    }
^-|CS||CP||AT|^B@2^Y@3 The art of deception in Contract Bridge play is simply to lead or play a card which tells your adversary a story quite different from your actual holding. You must always bear in mind that, when playing defensively, you are likely to mislead your Partner as well as the Declarer, and almost never make a deceptive play when it may plunge your Partner into trouble.|
