AT|

Let it be said here, lest some reader misunderstand, that this form of deception is entirely ethical—for the simple reason that it ^*Bdoes^*N mislead Partner as well as the Declarer. Any player may play any card he wishes, just so long as he follows suit when able. If he sees fit to depart from the usual or expected play, and makes an unusual or “false" play, that is his privilege. If his Opponent falls for the ruse, he cannot always be blamed, but the player who practiced the deception may well receive proper credit for his perspicacity in seeing the chance and his initiative in taking it. |
